<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
          <h2>SumPoints <span class="label label-default">beta</span></h2>
          <h4 class="section-subheading text-muted">A Place to Share and Bookmark Your Favourite Summary Points</h4>
      </div>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row text-center">
      <div class="col-md-4">
          <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
              <i class="fa fa-square fa-stack-2x text-inverse"></i>
              <i class="fa fa-search fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
          </span>

          <h4 class="service-heading">1. Find Something Cool</h4>
          <p class="text-muted">
            You've just read an <a href="http://www.newyorker.com/">awesome article</a> or a watched a brilliant <a href="http://www.ted.com/">TED</a> talk and there are a few key ideas you would like to save for future reference.
          </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
          <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
              <i class="fa fa-square fa-stack-2x text-inverse"></i>
              <i class="fa fa-list-ul fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
          </span>
          <h4 class="service-heading">2. SumPoint It</h4>
          <p class="text-muted">
            SumPoints is here to help you store those ideas. A <a href="/sumpoints">sumpoint</a> is simply a summary point of a key idea or concept you
            come across. The shorter it is, the better!
          </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
          <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
              <i class="fa fa-square fa-stack-2x text-inverse"></i>
              <i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
          </span>
          <h4 class="service-heading">3. Tag and Share It</h4>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Tag your sumpoints for future reference. When you like a sumpoint, it is added to your  
            <a href="users/library">library</a> which can be browsed by different tags. 
          </p>
      </div>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <!-- Sign up Button Area -->
